race.comment: DESERT DANCING (5) has gone under by less than a length her past couple, finishing strongly from wide draws in this grade. Now draws a better barrier which may see her sit a pair or two closer. Knocking on the door of another victory and looks ready to fire now back out to 1400m. HELLUVA GODDESS (4) won well two back before hitting the line with DESERT DANCING last start at the 2100m journey. She was a winner over 1300m first-up last campaign and the rise in trip looks a good move. May need some gaps to open but she has the ratings to fire should they come. SOLDIER OF GOD (8) will find this tougher than recent efforts, though he's turned in a couple of good ratings this time in work. He drops plenty of weight today and hits this ready to peak third-up. Can put his best foot forward. LATER ALLIGATOR (6) was too good last start at 80-1. Rates highly off that but needs to prove it wasn't a fluke. STREET BAND (1) can fire third-up and back in grade.
